The paper deals with the complexity of exploiting hidden structural properties in Boolean formulas, which is a topic closely related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the difficulty of determining satisfiability and backbone size, which are topics in logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses techniques from computational complexity and graph theory, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
